			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I had pretty much forgotten about systems built this way or designed to be able to do this, but it is just the old idea of docking a mobile phone/small computer with a dock station which would then allow it to interact with a more capable interface which could then interact with a much better system. <a href="http://www.linuxjournal.com/content/whats-dock" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.linuxjournal.com/content/whats-dock</a>  It won't ever be able to compete with a well designed work station, both in terms of resources and also likely security but it would be so cool for latency to be sufficiently low that lag was not noticeable over remote desktop and it was comfortable using programs like CAD/Video Editing/Photo Editing from anywhere without something gimped like browser software.</div>

